<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="641" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d641">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williams</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-05-01"><hi rend="italic">May 1, 1896</hi></date>.
                                (Received 3 p.m.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Urgent. Please instruct the United States minister at Madrid to request
                            Madrid Government to instruct Captain-General to observe strictly the
                            protocol in the trial of American citizens found on board <hi rend="italic">Competitor.</hi></p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>